{'problem_id': 'op_000067', 'moved_to': 'archived', 'target_row': {'id': 'op_000067', 'stmt': 'There is a finite branching automaton built only from subformulas of Γ ++ [A] such that, whenever residualAtomicState Γ A = some (Δ, s), acceptance from (Δ, s) in the residual graph is equivalent to acceptance in that finite automaton.', 'src': 'expand', 'mode': 'expand_candidate', 'summary_delta': 'This turns the new subformula control into a closed finite recognizer, which is exactly the next outward-looking abstraction suggested by the current frontier. It is stronger than a root-only bound and materially advances the program of internalizing residual recognition without relying on external graph machinery.', 'source_kind': 'expand_candidate', 'generated_from_source_id': 'op_000061', 'generated_from_source_kind': 'open_problem', 'priority': 'high', 'priority_rationale': 'An exact finite automaton built from sequent subformulas would replace external residual-graph acceptance with the desired canonical finite recognizer and would rewrite the theory summary.', 'failure_count': 2, 'parent_problem_ids': []}, 'solved_row': None, 'counterexample_row': None, 'duplicate_stmt_rows_removed': [], 'current_iteration': 4, 'picked_problem_id': 'op_000067', 'picked_problem_priority': 'high', 'result': 'stuck', 'verify_success': False, 'verify_error_excerpt': '', 'original_stmt': 'There is a finite branching automaton built only from subformulas of Γ ++ [A] such that, whenever residualAtomicState Γ A = some (Δ, s), acceptance from (Δ, s) in the residual graph is equivalent to acceptance in that finite automaton.', 'statement_prelude_code': 'def ResidualStateSubformulaBound (Γ : List Tp) (A : Tp) : AtomicResidualState → Prop\n  | (Δ, s) =>\n      (∀ B ∈ Δ, ∃ C ∈ Γ ++ [A], Subformula B C) ∧\n      (∃ C ∈ Γ ++ [A], occurs_atom s C)\n\nstructure FiniteAtomicBranchingAutomaton where\n  states : Finset AtomicResidualState\n  branches : AtomicResidualState → Finset (AtomicResidualState × AtomicResidualState)\n  branch_closed :\n    ∀ {p qq}, qq ∈ branches p → p ∈ states ∧ qq.1 ∈ states ∧ qq.2 ∈ states\n\ninductive FiniteAtomicBranchingAccepts (M : FiniteAtomicBranchingAutomaton) :\n    AtomicResidualState → Prop where\n  | base {s : String} (hmem : ([# s], s) ∈ M.states) :\n      FiniteAtomicBranchingAccepts M ([# s], s)\n  | step {p q1 q2 : AtomicResidualState}\n      (hbranch : (q1, q2) ∈ M.branches p)\n      (hleft : FiniteAtomicBranchingAccepts M q1)\n      (hright : FiniteAtomicBranchingAccepts M q2) :\n      FiniteAtomicBranchingAccepts M p', 'formalized_stmt': '∀ (Γ : List Tp) (A : Tp),\n  ∃ M : FiniteAtomicBranchingAutomaton,\n    (∀ p ∈ M.states, ResidualStateSubformulaBound Γ A p) ∧\n    ∀ (Δ : List Tp) (s : String),\n      residualAtomicState Γ A = some (Δ, s) →\n        (Δ, s) ∈ M.states ∧\n        (AtomicResidualGraphAccepts (Δ, s) ↔ FiniteAtomicBranchingAccepts M (Δ, s))', 'prelude_code': '', 'prover_statement_result': 'ok', 'prover_attempts_used': 2, 'priority_refresh_ran': True, 'priority_refresh_error': '', 'expand_candidates': [], 'stored_expand_rows': [], 'promoted_expand_rows': [], 'batch_generator_added_problem_rows': [], 'batch_generator_error': '', 'pending_expand_candidate_count': 2, 'archived_problem_count': 16, 'active_open_problem_count': 2, 'iteration': 4}
